=head1 DESCRIPTION

Configuration information for Amazon AppIntegrations to automatically
ingest content.

=head1 ATTRIBUTES


=head2 B<REQUIRED> AppIntegrationArn => Str

The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the AppIntegrations DataIntegration
to use for ingesting content.

=over

=item *

For Salesforce
(https://developer.salesforce.com/docs/atlas.en-us.knowledge_dev.meta/knowledge_dev/sforce_api_objects_knowledge__kav.htm),
your AppIntegrations DataIntegration must have an ObjectConfiguration
if objectFields is not provided, including at least C<Id>,
C<ArticleNumber>, C<VersionNumber>, C<Title>, C<PublishStatus>, and
C<IsDeleted> as source fields.

=item *

For ServiceNow
(https://developer.servicenow.com/dev.do#!/reference/api/rome/rest/knowledge-management-api),
your AppIntegrations DataIntegration must have an ObjectConfiguration
if objectFields is not provided, including at least C<number>,
C<short_description>, C<sys_mod_count>, C<workflow_state>, and
C<active> as source fields.

=item *

For Zendesk
(https://developer.zendesk.com/api-reference/help_center/help-center-api/articles/),
your AppIntegrations DataIntegration must have an ObjectConfiguration
if C<objectFields> is not provided, including at least C<id>, C<title>,
C<updated_at>, and C<draft> as source fields.

=item *

For SharePoint
(https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/sharepoint/dev/sp-add-ins/sharepoint-net-server-csom-jsom-and-rest-api-index),
your AppIntegrations DataIntegration must have a FileConfiguration,
including only file extensions that are among C<docx>, C<pdf>, C<html>,
C<htm>, and C<txt>.

=item *

For Amazon S3 (https://aws.amazon.com/s3/), the ObjectConfiguration and
FileConfiguration of your AppIntegrations DataIntegration must be null.
The C<SourceURI> of your DataIntegration must use the following format:
C<s3://your_s3_bucket_name>.

The bucket policy of the corresponding S3 bucket must allow the Amazon
Web Services principal C<app-integrations.amazonaws.com> to perform
C<s3:ListBucket>, C<s3:GetObject>, and C<s3:GetBucketLocation> against
the bucket.

=back



=head2 ObjectFields => ArrayRef[Str|Undef]

The fields from the source that are made available to your agents in
Wisdom. Optional if ObjectConfiguration is included in the provided
DataIntegration.

=over

=item *

For Salesforce
(https://developer.salesforce.com/docs/atlas.en-us.knowledge_dev.meta/knowledge_dev/sforce_api_objects_knowledge__kav.htm),
you must include at least C<Id>, C<ArticleNumber>, C<VersionNumber>,
C<Title>, C<PublishStatus>, and C<IsDeleted>.

=item *

For ServiceNow
(https://developer.servicenow.com/dev.do#!/reference/api/rome/rest/knowledge-management-api),
you must include at least C<number>, C<short_description>,
C<sys_mod_count>, C<workflow_state>, and C<active>.

=item *

For Zendesk
(https://developer.zendesk.com/api-reference/help_center/help-center-api/articles/),
you must include at least C<id>, C<title>, C<updated_at>, and C<draft>.

=back

Make sure to include additional fields. These fields are indexed and
used to source recommendations.



